---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Support — Matrix Digital Media"
  description="Get help with HiveHelper and other apps by Matrix Digital Media LLC."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="support-page">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="support-header">
        <a href="/" class="back-link">← Home</a>
        <h1>Support</h1>
        <p class="meta">We're here to help. Reach us at <a href="mailto:support@matrixnj.com">support@matrixnj.com</a></p>
      </div>

      <!-- CONTACT CARD -->
      <div class="contact-card">
        <div class="contact-info">
          <h2>Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            For bug reports, feature requests, account issues, or any other questions,
            email us directly. We typically respond within 1–2 business days.
          </p>
          <a href="mailto:support@matrixnj.com" class="btn-contact">
            Email Support
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="contact-detail">
          <p class="contact-label">Email</p>
          <p class="contact-value">support@matrixnj.com</p>
          <p class="contact-label">Response time</p>
          <p class="contact-value">1–2 business days</p>
          <p class="contact-label">Publisher</p>
          <p class="contact-value">Matrix Digital Media LLC</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <div class="faq-section">
        <div class="faq-header">
          <h2>HiveHelper — Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-list">

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How do I add a hive?</summary>
            <p>
              From the main screen, tap <strong>Add Hive</strong> and fill in the hive name
              and any optional details such as hive type and acquisition date. Your hive will
              appear on the home screen once saved.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How do I log an inspection?</summary>
            <p>
              Tap on any hive to open its detail view, then tap <strong>New Inspection</strong>.
              Work through the checklist — queen status, brood pattern, honey stores, and more.
              You can add notes and photos before saving.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What is included in the free tier?</summary>
            <p>
              The free tier includes up to <strong>2 hives</strong>, inspection history for the
              last <strong>60 days</strong>, and <strong>2 AI guidance</strong> uses. Upgrading
              to HiveHelper Pro removes all limits and unlocks unlimited hives, full history,
              and unlimited AI guidance.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How do I upgrade to Pro?</summary>
            <p>
              Tap the <strong>Upgrade</strong> prompt when you hit a free tier limit, or access
              it through the app settings. HiveHelper Pro is available as a monthly or annual
              subscription, both with a <strong>7-day free trial</strong>. Payment is processed
              securely through Apple.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How do I restore my purchase?</summary>
            <p>
              If you've previously subscribed and need to restore access, open the paywall screen
              and tap <strong>Restore Purchases</strong>. Make sure you're signed into the same
              Apple ID used for the original purchase.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How do I cancel my subscription?</summary>
            <p>
              Subscriptions are managed through your Apple ID. Go to
              <strong>Settings → [Your Name] → Subscriptions</strong> on your iPhone to view
              and cancel your HiveHelper Pro subscription at any time.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Is my data backed up?</summary>
            <p>
              All your inspection data and photos are stored locally on your device. Your data
              is included in your iPhone's standard iCloud or iTunes backup if you have backups
              enabled. We do not store your personal data on our servers.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What is AI guidance?</summary>
            <p>
              After completing an inspection, HiveHelper can provide AI-powered guidance based
              on your observations. This feature analyzes the data you entered and offers
              context-aware suggestions. An internet connection is required to use this feature.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What is frame photo analysis?</summary>
            <p>
              HiveHelper allows you to upload photos of hive frames for automated analysis via
              LandLens.ai. This feature is optional and only activates when you explicitly submit
              a photo for review. Submitted photos are processed by LandLens.ai per their
              privacy policy.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How do I delete my data?</summary>
            <p>
              You can delete individual inspections or hives from within the app. To remove all
              data, delete the app from your device. Since all data is stored locally, uninstalling
              the app permanently removes it.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>I found a bug or the app is crashing.</summary>
            <p>
              We're sorry to hear that. Please email us at
              <a href="mailto:support@matrixnj.com">support@matrixnj.com</a> with a description
              of the issue, your iPhone model, and iOS version. Screenshots or screen recordings
              are always helpful.
            </p>
          </details>

        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .support-page {
    padding-top: calc(var(--header-h) + 4rem);
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .support-header {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .back-link:hover { color: var(--text); }

  .support-header h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .meta {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .meta a {
    color: var(--accent-1);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  /* CONTACT CARD */
  .contact-card {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 5rem;
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .contact-info h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .contact-info p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .btn-contact {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #fff;
    background: var(--gradient);
    padding: 0.65rem 1.4rem;
    border-radius: 7px;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
  }

  .btn-contact:hover { opacity: 0.85; }

  .contact-label {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .contact-label:first-child { margin-top: 0; }

  .contact-value {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-section {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .faq-header {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .faq-header h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .faq-item {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 1.25rem 0;
  }

  .faq-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .faq-item summary {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text);
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }

  .faq-item summary::after {
    content: '+';
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: transform 0.2s;
  }

  .faq-item[open] summary::after {
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }

  .faq-item p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    padding-right: 2rem;
  }

  .faq-item a {
    color: var(--accent-1);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .contact-card {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
